HEADWORD: Proditorious
<hw>Prod`i*to"ri*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. OF.
<ets>proditoire</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Treacherous; perfidious; traitorous.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Daniel.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Apt to make unexpected revelations.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧Nature is <xex>proditorious</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Sir H. Wotton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Proditory</ent>⟦br⟧
